title: Kylie Jenner channels Ali G in yellow THICK! tracksuit

text:
She started out making waves in the make-up world with her Lip Kit. And now it seems Kylie Jenner is looking to make big inroads in the apparel market as well.
Photos featuring the 19-year-old reality starlet posed in her new tracksuit hit Instagram on Thursday.
And it looks like she got her inspiration from Ali G who wore a similar year several years ago.
Stylish! The 19-year-old reality starlet posed in her new tracksuit hit Instagram on Thursday
Two much: Kylie Jenner's new THICK! track suit looks inspired by Ali G
In the simple snaps, the youngest Jenner still manages to smolder in her baggy outfit.
Of course her famously voluptuous derriere makes an appearance in several of the shots, including one where she sits shooting a sultry look back at the camera.
Her behind is featured again in a standing shot of her with her hood removed, again faced away from the camera.
Another shot sees the girlfriend of Tyga simply standing, with her left hip pointed at the camera, perhaps trying to emphasize the 'THICK!' lettering down the outside of the leg.

Keeping it casual: While her raven locks were mostly covered by the large hood, a few shots did see her long tresses cascading down past her shoulders

Fashion has a new underdog: the humble hoodie. No longer resigned to slobbing round the house and duvet days, hoodies are being embraced by the fashion elite. We have Vetements to thank for this hoodie uprising: The brand that put streetwear back in the spotlight.
During fashion week, hoodies were styled under leather jackets, teamed with blazers, layered with coats or even paired with thigh high boots in the case of super blogger Chiara Ferragni.
Even Chanel, renowned for being one of the most elegant couture labels around, got in on the hoodie action for Autumn/Winter '16 - albeit with a luxe-looking, high-shine, pretty pink number. So kudos to Kylie Jenner for including one in her latest collection for The Kylie Shop, complete with matching joggers, that both feature the slogan 'thick' emblazoned on them… it hasn’t launched yet but keep an eye out.
